From: nvidia-driver-injector <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-12
Subject: [PATCH 0001/0007] tb-egpu: GPU-lost crash-safety cascade

Cluster P1 of the P1-P6 refactor. Foundation patch — defensive guards
against kernel panic when the GPU enters NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST state due
to a transient PCIe failure (the core upstream bug #979 fix).

Background
----------
On a Thunderbolt-attached eGPU, a single transient PCIe failure causes
osHandleGpuLost to declare PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST permanently. From that
point on, six distinct call-site cascades will, on the unpatched driver,
either deadlock the GPU lock or trip an NV_ASSERT and crash the kernel:

  1. osHandleGpuLost — commits to permanent loss on a single bad read.
  2. _rcdbAddRmGpuDump / nvdDumpAllEngines — try to crash-dump a GPU
     that is no longer there, fanning out RPC failures.
  3. clientFreeResource / serverFreeResourceTreeUnderLock — NV_ASSERT
     fires when the cleanup RPC returns NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST.
  4. _issueRpcAndWait — every subsequent RPC hangs the GPU lock for
     ~5s, starving the rest of the kernel.
  5. rpcRmApiFree_GSP — 107 cleanup-path NV_ASSERT sites would fire
     if the free RPC did not return NV_OK.
  6. osDevReadReg008/016/032 — once the bus is dead, every read waits
     for the hardware completion timeout (~50ms each).

This patch adds a single coherent set of guards covering all six call
sites, plus the kernel-open <-> RM bridge needed to propagate the
disconnect state between layers without leaking <linux/pci.h> into RM.

Consolidation
-------------
Replaces 10 legacy patches in patches/legacy/ (0001, 0002, 0003, 0004,
0006, 0008, 0010, 0011, 0012, 0013) with one structured patch.
Consolidation wins:

  * New header src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/include/nv-tb-egpu.h with
    shared constants TB_EGPU_GPU_LOST_RETRIES, TB_EGPU_GPU_LOST_DELAY_US,
    TB_EGPU_DEAD_BUS_U32/U16/U8, plus the TB_EGPU_LOG_ONCE() macro and
    the NV_ASSERT_OR_GPU_LOST() macro.

  * The six near-identical "static int s_..._logged = 0;" log-once
    latches that the legacy series duplicated are now one macro.

  * The 8/16/32-bit dead-bus check in osDevReadReg008/016/032 is now
    a single static inline tb_egpu_check_dead_bus() predicate; only
    the return constant differs per width.

  * The (NV_OK || GPU_IN_FULLCHIP_RESET || GPU_IS_LOST) resserv assert
    triplet collapses to NV_ASSERT_OR_GPU_LOST(status).

  * All AORUS branding / date stamps / per-Lever commentary stripped
    from log strings and replaced with a cross-reference to
    docs/lever-catalog.md. Log prefix is "tb_egpu: ".

  * Q-active's "pmc_boot_0_now != nvp->pmc_boot_0" sanity test is
    replaced with "pmc_boot_0_now == TB_EGPU_DEAD_BUS_U32", which is
    the semantically correct dead-bus signal regardless of whatever
    nvp->pmc_boot_0 happened to be at boot.

